Europa League]]: [[2016\u201317 UEFA Europa League|2016\u201317]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40004559 |title=Ajax 0\u20132 Manchester United |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=24 May 2017 |accessdate=11 August 2019}}<br />{{cite web |url=https://www.gettyimages.co.uk/detail/news-photo/axel-tuanzebe-and-anthony-martial-of-manchester-united-news-photo/687922948 |title=Ajax v Manchester United \u2013 UEFA Europa League Final |publisher=Getty Images |accessdate=11 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Aston Villa'''\n*[[EFL Championship play-offs]]: [[2019 English Football League play-offs#Championship|2019]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48331145 |title=Aston Villa 2\u20131 Derby County |first=Ian |last=Woodcock |website=BBC Sport |date=27 May 2019 |accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy#Players of the Year|Jimmy Murphy Young Player of the Year]]: [[2014\u201315 Manchester United F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=jmaward/>\n*[[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy#Players of the Year|Denzil Haroun Reserve Team Player of the Year]]: [[2016\u201317 Manchester United F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=dhaward/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[http://www.manutd.com/en/Players-And-Staff/First-Team/Axel-Tuanzebe.aspx Profile] at the Manchester United F.C. website\n*{{soccerbase}}\n\n{{Manchester United F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tuanzebe, Axel}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Ituri Province]]\n[[Category:Democratic Republic of the Congo footballers]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:England youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:England under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Manchester United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Aston Villa F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:English people of Democratic Republic of the Congo descent]]\n[[Category:Democratic Republic of the Congo emigrants to the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Axel Tuanzebe\n| image          = Manchester United v Wigan Athletic, January 2017 (33).JPG\n| image_size     = 200\n| caption        = Tuanzebe playing for [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in 2017\n| fullname       = Axel Tuanzebe<ref>{{cite web |title=Squads for 2016/17 Premier League confirmed |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/84136 |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2016 |accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1997|11|14|df=y}}<ref name=Soccerway/>\n| birth_place    = [[Bunia]], DR Congo\n| height         = 1.85 m<ref>{{cite news |first=Samuel |last=Luckhurst |title=Who is Axel Tuanzebe? Manchester United youngster in profile as he makes debut vs Wigan |url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/who-is-axel-tuanzebe-united-11620920?service=responsive |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |date=29 January 2017 |accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref>\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub    = [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]\n| clubnumber     = 38\n| youthyears1    = 2005\u20132015 |youthclubs1 = [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester United]]\n| years1         = 2015\u2013     |clubs1 = [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] |caps1 = 10 |goals1 = 0\n| years2         = 2018      |clubs2 = \u2192 [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] (loan)    |caps2 = 5  |goals2 = 0\n| years3         = 2018\u20132019 |clubs3 = \u2192 [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] (loan)    |caps3 = 25 |goals3 = 0<!-- he returned to Manchester United after the first loan, so these should be kept separate -->\n| nationalyears1 = 2016      |nationalteam1 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] |nationalcaps1 = 1 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2016\u20132017 |nationalteam2 = [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]] |nationalcaps2 = 9 |nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2017      |nationalteam3 = [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]] |nationalcaps3 = 1 |nationalgoals3 = 0\n| club-update    = 19:53, 7 December 2019 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 01:16, 14 November 2017 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Axel Tuanzebe''' (born 14 November 1997) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for {{English football updater|ManchesU}} club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].\n\nHe has represented England at [[England national under-19 football team|under-19]], [[England national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[England national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels.\n\n==Club career==\n===Manchester United===\n====Early years====\nTuanzebe was associated with the [[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester United academy]] from the age of eight.<ref name=manutdprofile>{{cite web |title=Axel Tuanzebe player profile page |url=http://www.manutd.com/en/Players-And-Staff/First-Team/Axel-Tuanzebe.aspx |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref> He was a member of [[SuperCupNI|Milk Cup]] winning youth sides in 2013 and 2014.<ref name=manutdprofile/> In May 2015, Tuanzebe won the Jimmy Murphy Young Player of the Year award.<ref name=jmaward>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Bostock |title=Tuanzebe is United's Young Player of the Year|url=http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Football-News/2015/May/Axel-Tuanzebe-wins-Jimmy-Murphy-Young-Player-of-the-Year-award.aspx |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=19 May 2015 |accessdate=15 November 2016}}</ref> Academy coach [[Paul McGuinness (footballer)|Paul McGuinness]] noted that Tuanzebe was the first first-year scholar to captain the under-18 side since [[Gary Neville]].<ref name=jmaward/>\n\nOn 31 October 2015, Tuanzebe was named on the substitutes bench for a match against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] in the [[Premier League]], the first time he had been a member of a first-team squad.<ref>{{cite news |first=Alistair |last=Magowan |title=Crystal Palace 0\u20130 Manchester United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34623912 |website=BBC Sport |date=31 October 2015 |accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Tuanzebe closer to realising his dream |url=http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Football-News/2015/Oct/axel-tuanzebe-aiming-to-become-manchester-united-leader.aspx?AL |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=31 October 2015 |accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n====2016\u201317 season====\nOn 29 January 2017, Tuanzebe made his Manchester United debut as a 68th-minute substitute, replacing [[Timothy Fosu-Mensah]] during a 4\u20130 [[2016\u201317 FA Cup|FA Cup]] victory over [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] at [[Old Trafford]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Manchester United 4\u20130 Wigan Athletic |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38709050 |website=BBC Sport |date=29 January 2017 |accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref> Four days later, he extended his contract at Manchester United until 2020, with the option of a further year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Axel Tuanzebe signs new Manchester United contract |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11667/10753590/axel-tuanzebe-signs-new-manchester-united-contract |publisher=Sky Sports |date=2 February 2017 |accessdate=2 February 2017}}</ref> On 7 May 2017, Tuanzebe started a senior match for the first time, in a 2\u20130 defeat against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news |first=Samuel |last=Lovett |title=Manchester United's Axel Tuanzebe 'chuffed' after making full debut and taking on Arsenal's Alexis Sanchez |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/manchester-united-news-axel-tuanzebe-full-debut-chuffed-taking-on-alexis-sanchez-a7724446.html |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |date=8 May 2017 |accessdate=14 May 2017}}</ref> He won the Denzil Haroun Reserve Team Player of the Year award in May 2017.<ref name=dhaward>{{cite news |first=Samuel |last=Luckhurst |title=Manchester United player Ander Herrera wins Player of the Year award|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-news-ander-herrera-13058295 |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |date=18 May 2017 |accessdate=19 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n====2017\u201318 season====\nTuanzebe made his first start of the season against [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] in the [[2017\u201318 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] on 24 October 2017, playing a key part in the second goal of the 2\u20130 victory.<ref>{{cite news |first=Dafydd |last=Pritchard |title=Swansea City 0\u20132 Manchester United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41647091 |website=BBC Sport |date=24 October 2017 |accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> On 5 December 2017, he made his European debut in a 2\u20131 victory over [[PFC CSKA Moscow|CSKA Moscow]] in the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Hafez |last=Shamoon |title=Manchester United 2\u20131 CSKA Moscow |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42229382|website=BBC Sport |accessdate=30 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Loans to Aston Villa====\nOn 25 January 2018, Tuanzebe joined [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] on [[Loan (sports)|loan]] for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Villa sign Man Utd defender Tuanzebe |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42818253 |website=BBC Sport |date=25 January 2018 |accessdate=25 January 2018 }}</ref> However, injuries meant he was only able to make five appearances before returning to Manchester United. He joined Aston Villa on loan again for the 2018\u201319 season.<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Tuanzebe heads back to Villa Park |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/axel-tuanzebe-rejoins-aston-villa-on-loan-for-season |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=6 August 2018 |accessdate=6 August 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nTuanzebe began his international career in June 2016, when he made his first appearance for England at [[England national under-19 football team|under-19]] level, against Mexico.<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Tuanzebe primed for first international tournament with England |url=http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Football-News/2016/Jun/young-manchester-united-defender-axel-tuanzebe-first-international-tournament-with-england-under-19s.aspx |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=7 June 2016 |accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref> He was a member of the [[England national under-20 football team|under-20]] squad which won all three matches at the Four Nations tournament in October 2016.<ref>{{cite news |title=England Under-20s win mini-tournament after 2\u20130 win over USA |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2016/oct/10/england-u20s-2-0-usa-report-101016 |publisher=The Football Association |date=10 October 2016 |accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref> Tuanzebe was withdrawn from selection for the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] due to club commitments.<ref>{{cite news |title=Man United's Axel Tuanzebe left out of England U20 World Cup squad|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/manchester-united/story/3121904/manchester-uniteds-axel-tuanzebe-left-out-of-england-u20-world-cup-squad |publisher=ESPN |date=8 May 2017 |accessdate=14 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 November 2017, Tuanzebe made his debut for [[England national under-21 football team|England under-21]] against [[Ukraine national under-21 football team|Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ukraine U21 0\u20132 England U21|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41884793 |website=BBC Sport |date=10 November 2017 |accessdate=14 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nTuanzebe's preferred position is at [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]], but he can also play as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]], and has featured as a [[Midfielder#Holding midfielder|holding midfielder]].<ref>{{cite news |first=James |last=Ducker |title=Axel Tuanzebe out of England U-20 squad as Mourinho wants him to play more for Man Utd |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2017/05/09/axel-tuanzebe-england-u-20-squad-mourinho-wants-play-man-utd/ |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=9 May 2017 |accessdate=14 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Axel Tuanzebe is coming of age at United |url=http://www.manutd.com/en/News-And-Features/Features/2017/May/axel-tuanzebe-if-you-are-good-enough-you-are-old-enough.aspx |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=25 May 2017 |accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref> His playing style has been compared to that of teammate [[Eric Bailly]] and Bayern Munich's [[Javi Mart\u00ednez]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Sam |last=Tighe |title=Manchester United's Axel Tuanzebe Has Hallmarks of Eric Bailly and Javi Martinez |url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2663571-manchester-uniteds-axel-tuanzebe-has-hallmarks-of-eric-bailly-and-javi-martinez |work=Bleacher Report |publisher=Turner |date=14 September 2016 |accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> Tuanzebe's performance on his first-team debut in a friendly against Wigan Athletic in July 2016 led manager [[Jos\u00e9 Mourinho]] to remark, \"10 minutes is enough! The potential is there, you see it immediately.\"<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Bajkowski |title=Mourinho praises Manchester United youngster Tuanzebe for his EIGHT minutes against Wigan |url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-axel-tuanzebe-mourinho-11624047 |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |date=16 July 2016 |accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nTuanzebe was born in [[Bunia]], Democratic Republic of the Congo.<ref name=Soccerway/> He attended [[St Cuthbert's RC High School]] in [[Rochdale]] and captained the Year 7 football team to the final of the English National Schools Cup at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]] in 2009.<ref name=earlylife>{{cite news |first=Samuel |last=Luckhurst |title=Manchester United youngster Axel Tuanzebe 'born for greatness' |url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manchester-united-youngster-axel-tuanzebe-10396435 |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |date=11 November 2015 |accessdate=15 November 2016}}</ref> In the same year, he was awarded Sports Boy of the Year by the Mayor of Rochdale.<ref name=earlylife/> He also represented his school in cross-country and triple-jump.<ref name=earlylife/> He is the younger brother of ex-[[Clitheroe F.C.|Clitheroe]] striker Dimitri Tuanzebe.<ref>{{cite news |first=Samuel |last=Luckhurst |title=Who is Axel Tuanzebe? Manchester United youngster in profile |url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/who-is-axel-tuanzebe-united-11620920 |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |date=29 January 2017 |accessdate=30 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2018, he broke the Guinness World Record for fastest time to clear a game of [[Hungry Hungry Hippos]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Charlotte |last=Dunker|title=Axel Tuanzebe breaks bizarre Guinness World Record on Manchester United pre-season tour|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/man-utd-tuanzebe-world-record-14923653 |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |date=18 July 2018 |accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 18 December 2019}}<ref name=Soccerway>{{Soccerway|420198|Axel Tuanzebe|accessdate=18 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and co