{"title_page": "Sumedh Mudgalkar", "text_new": "{{Short description|Indian actor and dancer}}\n{{BLP sources|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Sumedh Mudgalkar\n| other_names        = Beatking, Suma\n| birth_name         = Sumedh Vasudev Mudgalkar\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1996|11|2|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Nanded]], [[Maharashtra]], India\n| nationality        = Indian\n| residence          = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| education          = [[Maharashtra Institute of Technology]], [[Pune]]\n| occupation         = [[Actor]], [[Dancer]]\n<!-- | religion = Hinduism -->| image              = \n| caption            = \n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Sumedh Mudgalkar''' (born 2 November 1996) is an Indian film and television actor as well as a dancer. He made his television debut with the [[Channel V]] TV serial ''[[Dil Dosti Dance]]''. Sumedh is best known for his work on ''[[RadhaKrishn (TV series)|RadhaKrishn]]'' as [[Lord Krishna]] and [[Susima|Shushim]] in ''[[Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat|Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nSumedh Mudgalkar was born on 2 November 1996. He was born in [[Nanded]] and brought up in [[Pune]] and currently lives in [[Mumbai]] to pursue his career.{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Dance==\nMudgalkar has never undergone formal training. He has learned dance by watching performances on the internet. He made his dance debut on a Marathi reality show ''Dance Maharashtra Dance'' in 2012 and was one of the finalists. He appeared in ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' Season 4 in 2013 where he reached the finals. He also received the title of 'Beatking' by Shruti Merchant.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/150417/entertainment-bollywood/article/character-very-negative-and-tough-act-sumedh-mudgalkar|title=The character is very negative and tough to act: Sumedh Mudgalkar|website=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=27 May 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820165503/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150417/entertainment-bollywood/article/character-very-negative-and-tough-act-sumedh-mudgalkar|archive-date=20 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi-reviews/film-manjha/articleshow/59688509.cms|title=Manjha Review|website=India Times|access-date=27 May 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180506220421/https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi-reviews/film-manjha/articleshow/59688509.cms|archive-date=6 May 2018|df=}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMudgalkar made his acting debut in [[Channel V]]\u2019s ''[[Dil Dosti Dance]]'', a dance based youth show where he portrayed the role of Raghav aka Raghavendra Pratap. Then he became known for portraying the negative role of [[Susima|Yuvraj Sushim]] in the Indian historical drama ''[[Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/150417/entertainment-bollywood/article/character-very-negative-and-tough-act-sumedh-mudgalkar|title=The character is very negative and tough to act: Sumedh Mudgalkar|date=2015-04-17|work=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=2018-08-17|language=en}}</ref> \n\nSumedh next moved to the Marathi film industry with a cameo in the 2016 film ''[[Ventilator (2016 film)|Ventilator]]'' as Karan. He then appeared in ''[[Manjha]]'' which was his first film as a lead actor. He portrayed the role of a psychopath named Vicky.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/manjha-trailer-is-out/articleshow/59402741.cms|title=Jatin Wagle\u2019s intriguing Manjha trailer is out - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-08-17}}</ref> In 2018, Sumedh played the role of Salil in ''[[Bucket List (2018 film)|Bucket List]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/madhuri-dixit-nene-praises-sumedh-mudgalkar/articleshow/64033061.cms|title=Madhuri Dixit Nene praises Sumedh Mudgalkar - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-08-17}}</ref> \n\nSince 2018, Sumedh is playing the role of Lord [[Krishna]] in [[Swastik Productions|Swastik Picture's]] magnum opus ''[[RadhaKrishn (TV series)|Radhakrishn]]'' which started on 1 October on [[Star Bharat]]. He featured in a Marathi Music Album called ''Bekhabar Kashi Tu'' along with [[Sanskruti Balgude]].\n\n==Awards and nominations==\nHe was nominated in the category of Favourite Debut Actor in Maharashtracha Favourite Kon Awards 2017 for his role in Manjha. He won three awards at the Radio City Cine Awards - Best Actor, Best Male Debut and Best Villain for Manjha.\n\nSumedh was nominated in the category of Best Actor for film Manjha in Sanskruti Kaladarpan Awards 2018. Sumedh was nominated in the category of Best Actor for his debut film Manjha in the Marathi Filmfare Awards 2018.{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}} Fresh face of the year 2018 in ABP telebratione awards.\n\nIn 2019, he won the [[Indian Telly Award for Best Onscreen Couple|Indian Telly Award for Best Onscreen Couple (Jury)]] with his co-star Mallika Singh for their show ''[[RadhaKrishn]]''.<ref>{{Citation|title=Mallika Singh & Sumedh Mudgalkar Wins Best Jodi at Indian Telly Awards 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yY9GBwbsapE|language=en|access-date=2019-09-23}}</ref> Then, in 2019, he also won the Gold Award for Best Actor Debut for his role of Krishn in Radhakrishn.<ref name=\":0\">{{Citation|title=Sumedh Mudgalkar On Winning AWARD For Radha Krishna {{!}} 12th Gold Awards 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n3Pn1CThUak|language=en|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref> Also, he was the regional winner from India in the 2019 Asian Academy Creative Awards for best actor in a leading role for his role of Krishn.<ref>{{Citation|title=2019 Best Actor Leading Role {{!}} Regional Winners|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pSvsaGdHVmo|language=en|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref> He also won the Most Popular Jodi Award with Mallika Singh at the 2019 News India 18 Stardom Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newsd.in/saas-bahu-aur-devrani-stardom-awards-2019-here-the-complete-list-of-winners/|title=Saas Bahu aur Devrani Stardom Awards 2019: Here\u2019s the complete list of winners|date=2019-11-07|website=News and Analysis from India. A Refreshing approach to news.|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Language !! Notes\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Ventilator (2016 film)|Ventilator]]'' || Karan || rowspan=\"3\" | Marathi || \n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Manjha]]'' || Vicky ||Lead Role\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Bucket List (2018 film)|Bucket List]]'' || Salil ||\n|}\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Show !! Role !! Channel !! Notes  \n|-\n| 2013\u20132014 || ''[[Dil Dosti Dance]]'' || Raghavendra Pratap || [[Channel V India|Channel V]]\n|\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014 || ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' Season 4 || Contestant || [[Zee Tv]]\n|\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016 || ''[[Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat]]'' || [[Susima|Sushim]] || [[Colors TV]]\n|Negative Role\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present|| ''[[RadhaKrishn (TV series)|RadhaKrishn]]'' || [[Krishna|Lord Krishna]] || [[Star Bharat]]\n|Lead Role\n|-\n|2019|| ''[[Jag Janani Maa Vaishno Devi - Kahani Mata Rani Ki]]'' ||[[Narrator ]]\n|[[Star Bharat]]\n|Voice over \n|-\n\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n[[List of Indian television actors]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb name|7172762}}\n* {{Facebook|BeatkingSumedhMudgalkar}}\n* {{Twitter|Beatking_Sumedh}}\n* {{Instagram|beatking_sumedh}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mudgalkar, Sumedh}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Pune]]\n[[Category:Indian male dancers]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Marathi cinema]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Sumedh Mudgalkar\n| other_names        = Beatking, Suma\n| birth_name         = Sumedh Vasudev Mudgalkar\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1996|11|2|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Nanded]], [[Maharashtra]], India\n| nationality        = Indian\n| residence          = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| education          = [[Maharashtra Institute of Technology]], [[Pune]]\n| occupation         = [[Actor]], [[Dancer]]\n<!-- | religion = Hinduism -->| image              = \n| caption            = \n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Sumedh Mudgalkar''' (born 2 November 1996) is an Indian film and television actor as well as a dancer. He made his television debut with the [[Channel V]] TV serial ''[[Dil Dosti Dance]]''. Sumedh is best known for his work on ''[[RadhaKrishn (TV series)|RadhaKrishn]]'' as [[Lord Krishna]] and [[Susima|Shushim]] in [[Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat|Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat.]] \n\n==Personal life==\nSumedh Mudgalkar was born on 2 November 1996. He was born in [[Nanded]] and brought up in [[Pune]] and currently lives in [[Mumbai]] to pursue his career.{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Dance==\nMudgalkar has never undergone formal training. He has learned dance by watching performances on the internet. He made his dance debut on a Marathi reality show ''Dance Maharashtra Dance'' in 2012 and was one of the finalists. He appeared in ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' Season 4 in 2013 where he reached the finals. He also received the title of 'Beatking' by Shruti Merchant.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/150417/entertainment-bollywood/article/character-very-negative-and-tough-act-sumedh-mudgalkar|title=The character is very negative and tough to act: Sumedh Mudgalkar|website=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=27 May 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820165503/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150417/entertainment-bollywood/article/character-very-negative-and-tough-act-sumedh-mudgalkar|archive-date=20 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi-reviews/film-manjha/articleshow/59688509.cms|title=Manjha Review|website=India Times|access-date=27 May 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180506220421/https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi-reviews/film-manjha/articleshow/59688509.cms|archive-date=6 May 2018|df=}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMudgalkar made his acting debut in [[Channel V]]\u2019s ''[[Dil Dosti Dance]]'', a dance based youth show where he portrayed the role of Raghav aka Raghavendra Pratap. Then he became known for portraying the negative role of [[Susima|Yuvraj Sushim]] in the Indian historical drama ''[[Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/150417/entertainment-bollywood/article/character-very-negative-and-tough-act-sumedh-mudgalkar|title=The character is very negative and tough to act: Sumedh Mudgalkar|date=2015-04-17|work=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=2018-08-17|language=en}}</ref> \n\nSumedh next moved to the Marathi film industry with a cameo in the 2016 film ''[[Ventilator (2016 film)|Ventilator]]'' as Karan. He then appeared in ''[[Manjha]]'' which was his first film as a lead actor. He portrayed the role of a psychopath named Vicky.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/manjha-trailer-is-out/articleshow/59402741.cms|title=Jatin Wagle\u2019s intriguing Manjha trailer is out - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-08-17}}</ref> In 2018, Sumedh played the role of Salil in ''[[Bucket List (2018 film)|Bucket List]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/marathi/movies/news/madhuri-dixit-nene-praises-sumedh-mudgalkar/articleshow/64033061.cms|title=Madhuri Dixit Nene praises Sumedh Mudgalkar - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-08-17}}</ref> \n\nSince 2018, Sumedh is playing the role of Lord [[Krishna]] in [[Swastik Productions|Swastik Picture's]] magnum opus ''[[RadhaKrishn (TV series)|Radhakrishn]]'' which started on 1 October on [[Star Bharat]]. He featured in a Marathi Music Album called ''Bekhabar Kashi Tu'' along with [[Sanskruti Balgude]].\n\n==Awards and nominations==\nHe was nominated in the category of Favourite Debut Actor in Maharashtracha Favourite Kon Awards 2017 for his role in Manjha. He won three awards at the Radio City Cine Awards - Best Actor, Best Male Debut and Best Villain for Manjha.\n\nSumedh was nominated in the category of Best Actor for film Manjha in Sanskruti Kaladarpan Awards 2018. Sumedh was nominated in the category of Best Actor for his debut film Manjha in the Marathi Filmfare Awards 2018.{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}} Fresh face of the year 2018 in ABP telebratione awards.\n\nIn 2019, he won the [[Indian Telly Award for Best Onscreen Couple|Indian Telly Award for Best Onscreen Couple (Jury)]] with his co-star Mallika Singh for their show ''[[RadhaKrishn]]''.<ref>{{Citation|title=Mallika Singh & Sumedh Mudgalkar Wins Best Jodi at Indian Telly Awards 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yY9GBwbsapE|language=en|access-date=2019-09-23}}</ref> Then, in 2019, he also won the Gold Award for Best Actor Debut for his role of Krishn in Radhakrishn.<ref name=\":0\">{{Citation|title=Sumedh Mudgalkar On Winning AWARD For Radha Krishna {{!}} 12th Gold Awards 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n3Pn1CThUak|language=en|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref> Also, he was the regional winner from India in the 2019 Asian Academy Creative Awards for best actor in a leading role for his role of Krishn.<ref>{{Citation|title=2019 Best Actor Leading Role {{!}} Regional Winners|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pSvsaGdHVmo|language=en|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref> He also won the Most Popular Jodi Award with Mallika Singh at the 2019 News India 18 Stardom Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newsd.in/saas-bahu-aur-devrani-stardom-awards-2019-here-the-complete-list-of-winners/|title=Saas Bahu aur Devrani Stardom Awards 2019: Here\u2019s the complete list of winners|date=2019-11-07|website=News and Analysis from India. A Refreshing approach to news.|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Language !! Notes\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Ventilator (2016 film)|Ventilator]]'' || Karan || rowspan=\"3\" | Marathi || \n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Manjha]]'' || Vicky ||Lead Role\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Bucket List (2018 film)|Bucket List]]'' || Salil ||\n|}\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Show !! Role !! Channel !! Notes  \n|-\n| 2013\u20132014 || ''[[Dil Dosti Dance]]'' || Raghavendra Pratap || [[Channel V India|Channel V]]\n|\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014 || ''[[Dance India Dance]]'' Season 4 || Contestant || [[Zee Tv]]\n|\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016 || ''[[Chakravartin Ashoka Samrat]]'' || [[Susima|Sushim]] || [[Colors TV]]\n|Negative Role\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present|| ''[[RadhaKrishn (TV series)|RadhaKrishn]]'' || [[Krishna|Lord Krishna]] || [[Star Bharat]]\n|Lead Role\n|-\n|2019|| ''[[Jag Janani Maa Vaishno Devi - Kahani Mata Rani Ki]]'' ||[[Narrator ]]\n|[[Star Bharat]]\n|Voice over \n|-\n\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n[[List of Indian television actors]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb name|7172762}}\n* {{Facebook|BeatkingSumedhMudgalkar}}\n* {{Twitter|Beatking_Sumedh}}\n* {{Instagram|beatking_sumedh}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mudgalkar, Sumedh}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Pune]]\n[[Category:Indian male dancers]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Marathi ci